HEADWORD: Homatropine
<hw>Ho*mat"ro*pine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + <ets>atropine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An alkaloid, prepared from atropine, and from other sources. It is
chemically related to atropine, and is used for the same
purpose.</def>⟦br⟧
